  "body": "## Some truffle packages introduced undesired breaking changes after releasing Truffle 5\r\n\r\n### truffle-debugger\r\nThis package was released along with Truffle 5 including a breaking change: it uses `web3@^1.0.0-beta.37` but [it was tagged as a minor update (`4.0.3` ~> `4.1.0`)](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/compare/v4.1.14...v5.0.0#diff-d8e6ac7082f1bf264833376acf1135aeR3)\r\n\r\n### truffle-provider\r\nThis package is published under a major 0 version, which means that [it could introduce breaking changes](https://semver.org/#spec-item-4). But, there other packages like `truffle-core` using `truffle-provider` [accepting minor updates](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/v4.1.14/packages/truffle-core/package.json#L45), it should be declared with a tilde (`~`) instead of a caret (`^`).\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a sample project and init npm: `mkdir sample && cd sample && npm init -y`\r\n\r\n2. Declare the following dependencies in your package json:\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  ...,\r\n  \"dependencies\": {\r\n    \"ganache-cli\": \"^6.1.8\",\r\n    \"truffle-config\": \"^1.0.6\",\r\n    \"truffle-core\": \"^4.1.14\",\r\n    \"web3\": \"^0.20.6\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Install your dependencies: `npm i`\r\n\r\n4. Create a script `index.js` with the following content:\r\n```js\r\nasync function test() {\r\n  const TruffleConfig = require('truffle-config')\r\n  const config = TruffleConfig.detect({ logger: console })\r\n  config.network = 'local'\r\n\r\n  await new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\r\n    const TruffleEnvironment = require('truffle-core/lib/environment')\r\n    TruffleEnvironment.detect(config, function (error) {\r\n      if (error) reject(error)\r\n      else {\r\n        const Web3 = require('web3')\r\n        global.web3 = new Web3(config.provider)\r\n        resolve()\r\n      }\r\n    })\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  web3.eth.accounts.forEach(account => {\r\n    console.log(web3.eth.getBalance(account))\r\n  })\r\n}\r\n\r\ntest()\r\n  .then(console.log)\r\n  .catch(console.error)\r\n```\r\n\r\n5. Start a local ganache client: `npx ganache-cli --port 9545`\r\n\r\n6. Run the `index.js` script: `node index.js`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTo output the balances of all the accounts: \r\n```\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\nBigNumber { s: 1, e: 20, c: [ 1000000 ] }\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n``` \r\nTypeError: this.provider.sendAsync is not a function\r\n    at RequestManager.sendAsync (~/sample/node_modules/truffle-core/node_modules/web3/lib/web3/requestmanager.js:80:19)\r\n    at Object.get [as getNetwork] (~/sample/node_modules/truffle-core/node_modules/web3/lib/web3/property.js:116:33)\r\n    at detectNetworkId (~/sample/node_modules/truffle-core/lib/environment.js:55:20)\r\n    at Object.detect (~/sample/node_modules/truffle-core/lib/environment.js:75:5)\r\n    at Promise (~/sample/index.js:8:24)\r\n    at new Promise (<anonymous>)\r\n    at test (~/sample/index.js:6:9)\r\n    at Object.<anonymous> (~/sample/index.js:23:1)\r\n    at Module._compile (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:654:30)\r\n    at Object.Module._extensions..js (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:665:10)\r\n    at Module.load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:566:32)\r\n    at tryModuleLoad (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:506:12)\r\n    at Function.Module._load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:498:3)\r\n    at Function.Module.runMain (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:695:10)\r\n    at startup (internal/bootstrap/node.js:201:19)\r\n    at bootstrapNodeJSCore (internal/bootstrap/node.js:516:3)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Possible solution\r\n- Publish a new patch for all those truffle packages depending on `truffle-provider` with a caret, e.g. `truffle-core@4.1.14`, using a tilde (`~`) instead\r\n- Deprecate all new minor updates including a breaking change, e.g. `truffle-debugger@4.1.0`, and publish them as new major versions\r\n- Update Truffle 5 related packages to use the corresponding new published versions based on both steps above",
